<p>Islamic State said it carried out an overnight assault on Niger’s international airport and an adjacent air force base in Niamey, according to statements cited by multiple outlets. Niger’s state television said security forces responded quickly to the raid and reported that attackers were killed in the ensuing fighting. The incident underscores the strain Niger faces from armed groups operating in the Sahel, and it also fed into a political dispute: Niger’s military leader Abdourahamane Tiani alleged that France, Benin and Ivory Coast were involved, an accusation reported after the attack as regional tensions remain high.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/OWQzpr9oezCUnQFMQt_-VkJVu37z3DdyPgRghVIlSPp6Bn1aKCcALsswlVS87-bI1pq0_76inE2wRc0iTFXmJVOQdtGrbGcs_j-5CdavdYFtc_SxRks1HP7TLYHtz1dR0AptQX9GY4aYUB7whkRvbL55y5cbY4lQFmbklrGRQReZiVCIPrxDEmsxcvS2YjDW5SsvJ2jPaLhvOuQmgD7naTKYR3INIMY2ttTI3I9TnbdqCVGSmtE8SQgs0m70JzFW51dOUdFQv3-e8YD4MZnw' alt='Image published alongside reporting on the Niamey airport and air base attack.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Tactics used: The Guardian reported that motorcycle-riding assailants used heavy weapons and drones in what Islamic State described as a coordinated surprise strike.</li><li>Aircraft damage: The attack damaged planes linked to an Ivorian carrier and a Togolese airline, according to details reported by The Guardian.</li><li>Reported casualties: State television said four soldiers were wounded, while it also reported that 20 attackers were killed during the response.</li><li>Claim channel: Islamic State’s responsibility claim circulated via its propaganda outlet Amaq and was monitored by SITE Intelligence Group, which tracks jihadist communications.</li><li>Regional accusations: After the raid, Niger’s military ruler accused France, Benin and Ivory Coast of involvement, a claim reported without independent verification.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Islamic State (Sahel branch): The group claimed it carried out a “surprise and coordinated” operation against the airport and air base, disseminated via Amaq. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/jan/30/niger-airport-airbase-attack-islamic-state'>The Guardian</a>)</li><li>Nigerien authorities (state television): State TV said security forces reacted quickly and reported the killing of 20 attackers during the response. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/africa/article/3341894/islamic-state-claims-bold-attack-nigers-strategic-airport-hub'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Niger’s military leader Abdourahamane Tiani: Tiani alleged France, Benin and Ivory Coast were involved in the attack. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/30/isil-claims-deadly-attack-on-air-base-near-niger'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch'>Islamic State group claims responsibilty for a deadly attack on Niger&#x27;s airport in the capital</a> - youtube.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/islamic-state-claims-deadly-attack-on-airport-in-niger-capital'>Islamic State claims deadly attack on airport in Niger capital</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/1/30/isil-claims-deadly-attack-on-air-base-near-niger'>ISIL claims responsibility for Niger airport attack</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2026/jan/30/niger-airport-airbase-attack-islamic-state'>Islamic State claims attack on international airport and airbase in Niger</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/africa/article/3341894/islamic-state-claims-bold-attack-nigers-strategic-airport-hub'>Islamic State claims bold attack on Niger’s strategic airport hub</a> - scmp.com</li></ul>